{"schema": {"fields":[{"type":"integer","name":"index"},{"type":"string","name":"author_association"},{"type":"string","name":"body"},{"type":"datetime","name":"created_at"},{"type":"string","name":"html_url"},{"type":"integer","name":"id"},{"type":"string","name":"issue_url"},{"type":"string","name":"node_id"},{"type":"datetime","name":"updated_at"},{"type":"string","name":"url"},{"type":"string","name":"user"}],"pandas_version":"0.20.0","primaryKey":["index"]}, "data": [{"index":0,"author_association":"OWNER","body":"\/ping @zz85 @jahting\n","created_at":"2014-09-04T13:25:22.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/5265#issuecomment-54475343","id":54475343,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/5265","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDU0NDc1MzQz","updated_at":"2014-09-04T13:25:22.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/54475343","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars0.githubusercontent.com\/u\/97088?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjk3MDg4","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"mrdoob","type":"User","id":97088,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/orgs"}},{"index":1,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"> I ran into a problem because I have shapes described by curves and holes in 3D.\n\nAre the shapes and holes planar? If so, how do you know?\n","created_at":"2014-09-04T15:17:11.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/5265#issuecomment-54492806","id":54492806,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/5265","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDU0NDkyODA2","updated_at":"2014-09-04T15:17:11.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/54492806","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1000017?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/WestLangley","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwMDAwMTc=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"WestLangley","type":"User","id":1000017,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/orgs"}},{"index":2,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"It is by definition in the model file specs like that. Most of the time the points will be in X Y or Z plane, but in principle all planes are possible. Right now i use 3 of the points to find the normal of the plane and create a rotation matrix using (0,0,1) and the normal.\n\nSo say I have three points `a`, `b` and `c`\n\n```\nvar a, b, c, zAxis, normal, axis, theta, matrix;\n\nzAxis = new THREE.Vector3( 0, 0, 1 );\n\nnormal = new THREE.Vector3().crossVectors( \n    new THREE.Vector3().subVectors( b, a ), \n    new THREE.Vector3().subVectors( c, a ) \n).normalize();\n\naxis = new THREE.Vector3().crossVectors( normal, zAxis ).normalize();\n\ntheta = zAxis.angleTo( normal );\n\nmatrix = new THREE.Matrix4().makeRotationAxis( axis, theta );\n```\n\nI rotate all points using matrix. Then i define them to a 2d path and store the `z` value\/coordinate of one of the points for later use.\nI can do the same for holes and subtract them after rotation.\nIn the end I create a ShapeGeometry and move the whole thing `z` up and rotate with inverse matrix. \n\nThat works...\n\nEDIT:\n\nThe z i built in like this: `matrix.elements[14] = -z`\n","created_at":"2014-09-04T15:34:05.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/5265#issuecomment-54495736","id":54495736,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/5265","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDU0NDk1NzM2","updated_at":"2014-09-04T16:01:16.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/54495736","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Wilt\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Wilt\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars1.githubusercontent.com\/u\/2419627?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Wilt","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Wilt\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/Wilt","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Wilt\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI0MTk2Mjc=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Wilt\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Wilt\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Wilt\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"Wilt","type":"User","id":2419627,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Wilt\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Wilt\/orgs"}},{"index":3,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"OK, that is one way to do it.\n\nSo to paraphrase, you are requesting support for extrusion from a shape embedded in an arbitrary 3D plane, so you do not have to rotate the points first. Is that correct?\n","created_at":"2014-09-04T15:51:56.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/5265#issuecomment-54498735","id":54498735,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/5265","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDU0NDk4NzM1","updated_at":"2014-09-04T15:51:56.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/54498735","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1000017?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/WestLangley","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwMDAwMTc=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"WestLangley","type":"User","id":1000017,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/orgs"}},{"index":4,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"That is correct. And especially support to cut holes in those 3D planes. Because making the 3D geometries is not so complicated, but cutting holes and triangulating the result is a lot of work and right now all of that can only be done in 2D so I have to first translate everything to 2D shapes.\n","created_at":"2014-09-04T16:03:50.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/5265#issuecomment-54501561","id":54501561,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/5265","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDU0NTAxNTYx","updated_at":"2014-09-04T16:04:11.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/54501561","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Wilt\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Wilt\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars1.githubusercontent.com\/u\/2419627?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Wilt","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Wilt\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/Wilt","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Wilt\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI0MTk2Mjc=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Wilt\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Wilt\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Wilt\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"Wilt","type":"User","id":2419627,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Wilt\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Wilt\/orgs"}},{"index":5,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"What kind of model files are these, do you have a sample?\n\nAlso, I giving a little thought about the work I've done on extrusion, and I'm thinking the usefulness or practicalness of ExtrusionGeometry may be limited.\n\nMore often extrusion might be part of a modeller's function rather than a Primitive geometry, but ExtrusionGeometry might still be useful generating procedural geometries.\n","created_at":"2014-09-04T17:37:10.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/5265#issuecomment-54515159","id":54515159,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/